**who —** The Power Suit — Samus's Chozo-forged armor and the arsenal it accretes across Zebes — Varia and Gravity suits, Charge/Ice/Wave/Plasma beams, Super Missiles, Power Bombs, Space Jump, Screw Attack, Speed Booster, the Grapple Beam and X-Ray Scope

**what —** Samus's Chozo-forged armor and the arsenal it accretes across Zebes — Varia and Gravity suits, Charge/Ice/Wave/Plasma beams, Super Missiles, Power Bombs, Space Jump, Screw Attack, Speed Booster, the Grapple Beam and X-Ray Scope

**where —** SMT · Super Metroid — Nintendo, SNES 1994 (the third Metroid game)  Framework inputs: Super Metroid; Zebes; the baby Metroid; the Power Suit; the descent  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)

**why —** It is growth made the whole game: every upgrade is a new verb and a new door, the suit turning a trapped hunter into one who walks through walls she once could not.

**how —** Crystallized from Super Metroid (Nintendo, SNES 1994).

**◌ the mythos —** It is growth made the whole game: every upgrade is a new verb and a new door, the suit turning a trapped hunter into one who walks through walls she once could not. a being of the fortress-world Zebes and the silent hunt

